2
00:00:55,346 --> 00:00:57,075
<i>Tell me a fantasy.</i>

3
00:00:57,148 --> 00:00:58,547
Picture, if you will...

4
00:00:58,616 --> 00:01:00,277
a crisp winter afternoon.

5
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:03,013
You by a crackling fire
in a smoking jacket.

6
00:01:03,087 --> 00:01:05,021
Mmm. What color?

7
00:01:05,089 --> 00:01:06,954
Red... with blue satin lapels.

8
00:01:07,024 --> 00:01:10,619
- Mmm.
- And a zipper down the back.

9
00:01:10,694 --> 00:01:13,162
- What for?
- You'll see.

10
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:15,425
There's a light tapping
at the door.

11
00:01:15,499 --> 00:01:19,026
"Who's there?" you say,
checking your zipper.

12
00:01:19,103 --> 00:01:22,038
You saunter to the door,
straightening your ascot...

13
00:01:22,106 --> 00:01:24,255
and casually
slide back the bolt.

14
00:01:24,388 --> 00:01:26,481
Come on! Who is it?

15
00:01:26,557 --> 00:01:29,151
- Lana Turner.
- Wearing?

16
00:01:29,227 --> 00:01:33,994
An angora sweater...
with a zipper down the back.

17
00:01:34,065 --> 00:01:36,158
- What for?
- You'll see.

18
00:01:36,234 --> 00:01:38,896
Go on.

19
00:01:38,970 --> 00:01:42,633
She throws her arms around you.
But you push her away!

20
00:01:42,707 --> 00:01:44,698
I push her away? For what?

21
00:01:44,775 --> 00:01:48,871
Your smoking jacket
is covered with angora lint.

22
00:01:48,946 --> 00:01:51,608
In a fit of pique, she leaves.

23
00:01:51,682 --> 00:01:54,708
That's it? The end?

24
00:01:54,785 --> 00:01:57,413
- That's it.
- But what about the zippers down the back?

25
00:01:57,488 --> 00:01:59,979
- They didn't catch on.
- Oh, I don't believe it!

26
00:02:00,057 --> 00:02:02,252
I had Lana Turner in a fantasy
with a sweater...

27
00:02:02,326 --> 00:02:04,886
with a zipper down the back
and I let her get away?

28
00:02:04,962 --> 00:02:07,430
- You always were short on zip.
- [Whines]

29
00:02:07,498 --> 00:02:10,126
Then the colonel said,
"Whatever you do, don't tell Burns."

30
00:02:10,201 --> 00:02:12,863
- What? What? What?
- Oh, I'm sorry, Frank. I promised.

31
00:02:12,937 --> 00:02:14,871
Why don't
you guys like me, huh?

32
00:02:14,939 --> 00:02:17,237
Because you're a lousy doctor
and a rotten person.

33
00:02:17,308 --> 00:02:19,242
- Aside from that.
- Well, there's your pimples.

34
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:23,804
My pores won't close! Aw, come on, guys.
I'll show you my present.

35
00:02:23,881 --> 00:02:26,008
- Show us your present first.
- Okay.

36
00:02:28,286 --> 00:02:30,345
[Laughs]
You see?

37
00:02:30,421 --> 00:02:34,653
You roll the B.B.'s around
and you try and get 'em in the holes.

38
00:02:34,725 --> 00:02:37,250
Now tell me what the colonel
said not to tell me.

39
00:02:37,328 --> 00:02:41,458
[Inhales] He asked Father Mulcahy
to pray for your pores.

40
00:02:41,532 --> 00:02:43,466
Smart aleck!

41
00:02:43,534 --> 00:02:45,468
- [B.J.] Can't we play with your game?
- No!

42
00:02:45,536 --> 00:02:48,164
Nobody makes fun of my skin
and gets away with it.

43
00:02:48,239 --> 00:02:50,537
Besides, it's from a former receptionist.
[Laughs]

44
00:02:50,608 --> 00:02:53,600
Good picture of her.
Nice B.B.'s.

45
00:02:53,678 --> 00:02:56,943
- No dibs on my game.
- Show you my ingrown toenail.

46
00:02:57,014 --> 00:02:59,209
I looked at it
while you were asleep.

47
00:02:59,283 --> 00:03:01,547
Well, then you owe me!

48
00:03:01,619 --> 00:03:05,385
Oh, buzz off!
Aha! Got one B.B. In.

49
00:03:05,456 --> 00:03:07,549
- Belly button?
- Uh-uh. Right ear.

50
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:10,685
- Tilt!
- ## [Whistles]

51
00:03:13,564 --> 00:03:17,000
Well, we managed to kill another
five minutes of the war.

52
00:03:17,068 --> 00:03:19,195
Wanna catch a rat
and make it a pet?

53
00:03:19,270 --> 00:03:22,967
Nah. It's not fair to the rat to keep it
in a small furnished apartment.

54
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:26,009
- You kept a cockroach.
- It was paper-trained.

55
00:03:26,077 --> 00:03:29,843
Hey, the <i>Times.</i>
Listen to this.

56
00:03:29,914 --> 00:03:33,714
"Senator Joseph McCarthy claims
Communists have infiltrated the military."

57
00:03:33,784 --> 00:03:36,651
I knew it. Every time
they mention those pinkos, I see red.

58
00:03:36,721 --> 00:03:38,746
Relax, Comrade.

59
00:03:38,889 --> 00:03:41,016
- Aaah! Oh, ho-ho! Bingo!
- What? What? What?

60
00:03:41,092 --> 00:03:43,492
- We struck oil and gold!
- What is it?

61
00:03:43,561 --> 00:03:46,155
- The <i>Times</i> crossword puzzle.
- Oh, fantastic!

62
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:49,427
Okay. One down.
Four letters. "Young fellow."

63
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:52,333
- Uh, "chap."
- Right.

64
00:03:52,403 --> 00:03:55,270
One across.
"Member of the company."

65
00:03:55,339 --> 00:03:57,500
- Four letters. Starts with a "C."
- Uh...

66
00:03:57,575 --> 00:03:59,907
- "Cast."
- Good.

67
00:03:59,977 --> 00:04:02,468
It's kid stuff.
Ha-ha!

68
00:04:02,546 --> 00:04:05,515
Got a B.B. Right in her eyeball.
[Giggles]

69
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:08,416
[Mulcahy]
Six-letter word. "Burrowing animal."

70
00:04:08,486 --> 00:04:11,182
- [Hawkeye] "Frank Burns."
- Too many letters.

71
00:04:11,255 --> 00:04:15,521
But close. Let's see.
A burrowing animal. A Hepler!

72
00:04:15,593 --> 00:04:18,619
- A what?
- Louis Hepler. Kid I went to high school with.

73
00:04:18,696 --> 00:04:21,062
Got expelled for burrowing
into the girls' washroom.

74
00:04:21,132 --> 00:04:25,466
- Only guy I ever knew who got
flushed out of high school.
- I don't think that's it.

75
00:04:25,536 --> 00:04:27,527
- "Ferret"!
- I wonder how he thought of that.

76
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:29,539
[Margaret]
Probably looked in the mirror.

77
00:04:29,607 --> 00:04:32,132
- The third letter is a "P."
- How about "gopher"?

78
00:04:32,209 --> 00:04:35,645
Bingo!
Uh, I'm sorry.

79
00:04:35,713 --> 00:04:37,840
Give us another one.

80
00:04:37,915 --> 00:04:42,682
Six letters, begins with "G,"
and means scandalmonger.

81
00:04:42,753 --> 00:04:46,348
- "Gossip."
- Give that lady 14 inches
of perforated intestine.

82
00:04:46,424 --> 00:04:48,483
- What would I do with that?
- Make a clarinet.

83
00:04:48,559 --> 00:04:52,017
- [Laughs]
- Margaret, uh, trim that rough edge there.

84
00:04:52,096 --> 00:04:54,223
- I don't wanna leave a bad scar.
- Yes, Doctor.

85
00:04:54,298 --> 00:04:58,325
- Why be so careful with
a Chinese prisoner of war?
- Frank, he's a human being.

86
00:04:58,402 --> 00:05:00,870
