- Frank?

96
00:05:27,164 --> 00:05:30,190
So you can take all the credit, I suppose, huh?
[Chuckles]

97
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:34,033
I'm a perfectly competent doctor...
122nd in a class of 200...

98
00:05:34,105 --> 00:05:36,335
and capable
of handling my own cases.

99
00:05:36,407 --> 00:05:38,398
Just asking.

100
00:05:38,476 --> 00:05:41,570
- We're losing him, Doctor.
- Pierce! Help!

101
00:05:44,248 --> 00:05:46,182
[Giggling]

102
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:48,184
What are you cackling at,
Major Burns?

103
00:05:48,252 --> 00:05:51,744
Nothing. Just a game to test your manual
dexterity. It's excellent for surgeons.

104
00:05:51,822 --> 00:05:54,290
How childish!

105
00:05:54,358 --> 00:05:56,292
- That's pornographic.
- What is?

106
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,385
That girl.
She's practically nude.

107
00:05:58,462 --> 00:06:00,623
There's nothing wrong
with the human body, Margaret.

108
00:06:00,698 --> 00:06:03,132
And there's certainly nothing wrong with hers.
[Laughs]

109
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:07,603
Oh, you have no idea how silly you look
drooling over that disgusting toy.

110
00:06:07,671 --> 00:06:10,265
Well, a man has to have something.
I'm very lonely, Margaret.

111
00:06:10,341 --> 00:06:13,333
You deserve to be.
Look at that skimpy outfit she's wearing.

112
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:17,039
- I could buy you one like it.
- How would you like that
game jammed in your ear?

113
00:06:17,114 --> 00:06:20,208
Oh, don't make me nervous, Margaret.
I'll shake my B.B.'s loose.

114
00:06:20,284 --> 00:06:22,844
It's too late, Frank.

115
00:06:24,889 --> 00:06:28,154
All my life I've never been able to finish
a <i>Times</i> crossword puzzle.

116
00:06:28,225 --> 00:06:30,989
- One more word is all we need.
- Shoot.

117
00:06:31,061 --> 00:06:32,995
Thirty-eight across.
Five letters.

118
00:06:33,063 --> 00:06:34,997
Begins with a "V."
"Means a Yiddish bedbug."

119
00:06:35,065 --> 00:06:39,764
Let's see. Yiddish, Jewish, Hebrew...
God knows I've read my Bible.

120
00:06:39,837 --> 00:06:42,465
- Did Moses speak Yiddish?
- Only when he was playing pinochle.

121
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:44,474
- Oh, Father.
- Yes, Hawk?

122
00:06:44,542 --> 00:06:46,874
You know the term
in Yiddish for bedbug?

123
00:06:46,944 --> 00:06:52,814
In the Bible, there are hosts of locusts,
plagues of vermin, and hordes of scorpions.

124
00:06:52,883 --> 00:06:55,784
Boy, a lot of bedbugs
in those days.

125
00:06:55,853 --> 00:06:57,821
Five letters.
Starts with a "V."

126
00:06:57,888 --> 00:07:00,618
Why don't you ask Corporal Shapiro?
He's sitting right over there.

127
00:07:00,691 --> 00:07:03,216
- Oh, thanks, Padre.
- <i>Ma</i>z<i>el tov.</i>

128
00:07:05,396 --> 00:07:08,126
- Uh, Shapiro.
- [Southern Accent] Oh, hi, y'all, Doc.

129
00:07:08,199 --> 00:07:11,430
You know the Yiddish word
for bedbug?

130
00:07:11,502 --> 00:07:15,666
Sorry, Captain. We been seven generations
in Georgia just raisin' cotton.

131
00:07:15,739 --> 00:07:18,207
And old times there are soon forgotten.
<i>Ma</i>z<i>el tov.</i>

132
00:07:18,275 --> 00:07:21,301
- How's that, Captain?
- Forget it.

133
00:07:21,378 --> 00:07:23,312
Maybe that's it.

134
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:25,974
- [With Southern Accent] Bedbug.
- What did Shapiro say?

135
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:28,075
He can't get the cotton
out of his mouth.

136
00:07:28,152 --> 00:07:32,179
Thank you, dear Lord, for giving us
this bounty during trying times. Amen.

137
00:07:32,256 --> 00:07:34,383
So that's what this is...
roast bounty.

138
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,688
<i>[Hawkeye]</i>
<i>Does that help?</i>

139
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,694
With a touch of ketchup.

140
00:07:38,762 --> 00:07:41,993
- Thank God for ketchup.
- He just did.

141
00:07:42,066 --> 00:07:46,059
I had a friend in college used to make
tomato soup out of ketchup and hot water.

142
00:07:46,136 --> 00:07:48,900
That's it!
Tippy Brooks is the answer.

143
00:07:48,973 --> 00:07:51,908
- What's the question?
- The puzzle. He's a crossword freak.

144
00:07:51,976 --> 00:07:53,910
He does
the double crostic in ink.

145
00:07:53,978 --> 00:07:56,572
- Oh, your friend the doctor on the <i>Essex.</i>
- Right!

146
00:07:56,647 --> 00:07:58,911
- The <i>Essex</i> is in Pusan Harbor.
- <i>[Hawkeye] I know!</i>

147
00:07:58,983 --> 00:08:01,975
- Radar, let's get on the horn.
- I haven't checked my bread for maggots.

148
00:08:02,052 --> 00:08:04,680
- Tell 'em you'll be right back.
- Come on.

149
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:11,254
I've got a guy in Seoul contacting the <i>Essex.</i>
He's a radioman first class.

150
00:08:11,328 --> 00:08:14,354
- <i>[Hawkeye] That's nice for his mother.</i>
- I only know him by voice.

151
00:08:14,431 --> 00:08:18,060
Stevens? Yeah, yeah!
I can hardly hear ya.

152
00:08:18,135 --> 00:08:21,229
Oh, oh, oh, oh. His oatmeal cookie
caught fire in the ashtray.

153
00:08:21,305 --> 00:08:23,671
- Gracious living.
- <i>Did you put it out?</i>

154
00:08:23,741 --> 00:08:26,642
Oh, he lost his cookie,
but he saved his raisins.

155
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,678
How come we don't
get raisins?

156
00:08:28,746 --> 00:08:30,873
I saw some the other day,
but they flew away.

157
00:08:30,948 --> 00:08:34,281
That's right. Lieutenant Brooks.
He's a doctor on the <i>Essex.</i>

158
00:08:34,351 --> 00:08:38,720
Uh-huh? Stevens?
Stevens, I can hardly hear y...

159
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,848
Oh, boy! He's fading.
Hawkeye...

160
00:08:40,924 --> 00:08:44,223
put your right hand on the wastebasket
and hold your left hand out.

161
00:08:44,295 --> 00:08:46,729
- Will this blow out the lightbulb in my navel?
- Uh-uh.

162
00:08:46,797 --> 00:08:50,597
B.J., you hold his hand and hold
your left hand straight up.

163
00:08:50,668 --> 00:08:53,102
- You've got sweaty palms.
- I'm new in radio.

164
00:08:53,170 --> 00:08:57,106
Stevens? Right.
Okay, hold on.

165
00:08:57,174 --> 00:08:59,165
Uh, Doctor Brooks
is in surgery.

166
00:08:59,243 --> 00:09:01,905
Tell him Hawkeye Pierce,
MASH 4077, called.

167
00:09:01,979 --> 00:09:03,913
- And needs his help desperately.
- Right.

168
00:09:03,981 --> 00:09:09,317
Uh, Dr. Hawkeye Pierce, MASH 4077,
needs his help real bad. Right.

169
00:09:09,386 --> 00:09:11,479
- Thanks, kid.
- What? What?

170
00:09:11,555 --> 00:09:14,183
I can't hear ya.
My aerials walked out on me.

171
00:09:14,358 --> 00:09:16,292
[Straining]

172
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,521
Ah! Whew.

173
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:25,465
<i>[Metal Clanking]</i>

174
00:09:32,109 --> 00:09:34,373
<i>[Metal Clanking]</i>

175
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:38,775
[Clanks]

176
00:09:42,286 --> 00:09:44,254
Hi, Klinger.
How's it goin'?

177
00:09:44,321 --> 00:09:47,085
- I'm eating a jeep.
- Good.

178
00:09:48,859 --> 00:09:50,952
[Gulps]

179
00:09:51,028 --> 00:09:52,962
[Regurgitates]

180
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,555
[Gulps]

181
00:10:02,773 --> 00:10:05,037
- Colonel?
- Radar, no interoffice running.

182
00:10:05,109 --> 00:10:08,408
- Yes, sir.
- Good news. The Chinese have
agreed to a prisoner exchange.

183
00:10:08,479 --> 00:10:10,413
Terrific.
Sir, we got big problems.

184
00:10:10,481 --> 00:10:12,472
Hawkeye locked Burns
in the nurses' latrine?

185
00:10:12,549 --> 00:10:14,608
- No, sir. That was last Friday.
- Time flies.

186
00:10:14,685 --> 00:10:16,653
- Yes. It's Klinger.
- Rats in his blue wig?

187
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:20,349
- No, sir. He's outside having a picnic.
- Annoying but tolerable.

188
00:10:20,424 --> 00:10:22,415
He's eating a jeep.

189
00:10:23,494 --> 00:10:25,462
- I beg your pardon?
- He's eating a jeep.

190
00:10:25,529 --> 00:10:28,396
- Which one?
- The one with the squeaky seats.

191
00:10:28,465 --> 00:10:31,491
[Exhales]
Finally came up with something fresh.

192
00:10:31,568 --> 00:10:33,661
How do you see through
those filthy glasses?

193
00:10:33,737 --> 00:10:35,621
I know where everything is.

194
00:10:39,892 --> 00:10:41,951
<i>There he is, sir.</i>

195
00:10:44,096 --> 00:10:46,428
"A" for effort, Klinger.
But it won't work.

196
00:10:46,498 --> 00:10:48,693
Watch this.

197
00:10:50,236 --> 00:10:52,261
[Gulping]

198
00:10:54,406 --> 00:10:56,374
Oh, wow! Right down.

199
00:10:56,442 --> 00:10:59,240
Dip it in a little 30-weight motor oil,
pop it in...

200
00:10:59,311 --> 00:11:02,542
and let it slide down the gullet
like a bluepoint oyster.

201
00:11:02,615 --> 00:11:04,583
Colonel, he's crazy!

202
00:11:04,650 --> 00:11:08,518
See! I got a witness! You gotta give me
a Section Eight and send me home.

203
00:11:08,587 --> 00:11:11,988
- No dice.
- If you don't throw me out for being a nut...

204
00:11:12,057 --> 00:11:13,888
<i>you're nuttier</i>
<i>than I am!</i>

205
00:11:13,959 --> 00:11:16,519
- Sir.
- Sir, he just ate a piece of iron.

206
00:11:16,595 --> 00:11:19,894
- That, too, shall pass.
- Okay.

207
00:11:19,965 --> 00:11:21,899
The second course.

208
00:11:31,477 --> 00:11:33,411
How about that?

209
00:11:33,479 --> 00:11:35,811
That dumb wiper
never worked anyway.

210
00:11:35,881 --> 00:11:38,714
Cute idea, Klinger.
Now cancel the picnic.

211
00:11:38,784 --> 00:11:42,379
You don't believe I'm gonna
eat this jeep, do you, sir?

212
00:11:42,454 --> 00:11:44,786
Let's say I find it
hard to swallow.

213
00:11:44,857 --> 00:11:47,087
Stick around, Colonel,
and watch it disappear.

214
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:50,128
If you want to ruin your stomach,
eat in the Mess Tent.

215
00:11:50,195 --> 00:11:54,063
I need this jeep
for the prisoner exchange.

216
00:11:54,133 --> 00:11:58,365
Just once I'd like to sit down to a meal
and not be interrupted by business.

217
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:05,677
- Gee, you think he's gonna be all right?
- Oh, he'll be fine.

218
00:12:05,744 --> 00:12:08,577
We may have to slap him on the rack
and give him a lube job.

219
00:12:08,647 --> 00:12:11,810
- But he was eating nuts.
- Squirrels do it all the time.

220
